webpackJsonp([8566180198644],{5609:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{post:{html:'<p>I just rearranged my <a href="http://www.papascott.de/referers.php">referers page</a> to sort chronologically, which seems to make more sense for a site with little traffic like this one.  I\'m still using <a href="http://ranchero.com/php/rollingreferers/">Brent\'s code</a>, but added a MAX(d) column to the SQL query, and sort on it: </p>\n<p><code>SELECT DISTINCT url, COUNT(*) as ct, MAX(d) as maxd from referers GROUP BY url ORDER BY maxd DESC, url;</code></p>\n<p>I could do some more intelligent things with the URLs (like sort out duplicates and highlight the really <a href="http://searchrequests.weblogs.com/">disturbing</a> Google queries), but maybe another day.</p>',fields:{title:"What Have You Done For Me Lately?",date:"12 Jun 2002",url:"https://papascott.de/2002-06-12-what-have-you-done-for-me-lately/"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/2002-06-12-what-have-you-done-for-me-lately/",prev:{fields:{title:"He's Back!",date:"12 Jun 2002",slug:"/2002-06-12-hes-back/"}},next:{fields:{title:"World Cup: How German soccer fans feel",date:"12 Jun 2002",slug:"/2002-06-12-world-cup-how-german-soccer-fans-feel/"}}}}}});
